nodes.text: There should be no discrimination in how a passenger is bumped or compensated just because they may have paid less for a ticket or used frequent flyer miles.
travellots(475): There should be no discrimination in how a passenger is bumped or compensated just because they may have paid less for a ticket or used frequent flyer miles.
Annot: There should be no discrimination in how a passenger is bumped or compensated just because they may have paid less for a ticket or used frequent flyer miles.
Airline tickets are not lottery tickets.
travellots(475): Airline tickets are not lottery tickets.
Annot: Airline tickets are not lottery tickets.
One does not purchase a ticket hoping to reach a certain destination.
travellots(475): One does not purchase a ticket hoping to reach a certain destination.
Annot: One does not purchase a ticket hoping to reach a certain destination.
Same as if one pays $4 for a cup of coffee or $1, the cup is supposed to have coffee in it.
travellots(475): Same as if one pays $4 for a cup of coffee or $1, the cup is supposed to have coffee in it.
Annot: Same as if one pays $4 for a cup of coffee or $1, the cup is supposed to have coffee in it.
The price does not dictate that "maybe" you will get the product or service.
travellots(475): The price does not dictate that "maybe" you will get the product or service.
Annot: The price does not dictate that "maybe" you will get the product or service.
Also, the airline decides what prices or miles are used to purchase a promise to get you from point A to point B.
travellots(475): Also, the airline decides what prices or miles are used to purchase a promise to get you from point A to point B.
Annot: Also, the airline decides what prices or miles are used to purchase a promise to get you from point A to point B.
If they can not afford to give  a ticket for that price, they should not sell it.
travellots(475): If they can not afford to give  a ticket for that price, they should not sell it.
Annot: If they can not afford to give  a ticket for that price, they should not sell it.
When you reserve a ticket, the assumption is that you will be taken from point A to point B by the times given by the airline.
travellots(475): When you reserve a ticket, the assumption is that you will be taken from point A to point B by the times given by the airline.
Annot: When you reserve a ticket, the assumption is that you will be taken from point A to point B by the times given by the airline.
A passenger does not purchase a ticket just to see if maybe they can get somewhere because they have nothing better to do.
travellots(475): A passenger does not purchase a ticket just to see if maybe they can get somewhere because they have nothing better to do.
Annot: A passenger does not purchase a ticket just to see if maybe they can get somewhere because they have nothing better to do.
If compensation is not high enough, the airlines will not have an incentive to schedule properly.
travellots(475): If compensation is not high enough, the airlines will not have an incentive to schedule properly.
Annot: If compensation is not high enough, the airlines will not have an incentive to schedule properly.
It is not fair to allow airlines to discriminate against lower fared passengers or "free" passengers
travellots(475): It is not fair to allow airlines to discriminate against lower fared passengers or "free" passengers
Annot: It is not fair to allow airlines to discriminate against lower fared passengers or "free" passengers
since it is the airline, not the passenger or government, who gave that passenger a seat.
travellots(475): since it is the airline, not the passenger or government, who gave that passenger a seat.
Annot: since it is the airline, not the passenger or government, who gave that passenger a seat.
Otherwise, airlines can advertise low fares or con you into using them to build up your "miles" and then always bump you for someone who paid more.
travellots(475): Otherwise, airlines can advertise low fares or con you into using them to build up your "miles" and then always bump you for someone who paid more.
Annot: Otherwise, airlines can advertise low fares or con you into using them to build up your "miles" and then always bump you for someone who paid more.
In away,it is the same as being able to increase your ticket price anytime after purchase.
travellots(475): In away,it is the same as being able to increase your ticket price anytime after purchase.
Annot: In away,it is the same as being able to increase your ticket price anytime after purchase.
When you are bumped, there are a lot of hidden extra costs
travellots(475): When you are bumped, there are a lot of hidden extra costs
Annot: When you are bumped, there are a lot of hidden extra costs
It irks me that airlines seem to be treating passengers more and more as if they have nothing better to do but wait around in airports and not get to where the airline promised to bring them.

travellots(475): It irks me that airlines seem to be treating passengers more and more as if they have nothing better to do but wait around in airports and not get to where the airline promised to bring them.
Annot: It irks me that airlines seem to be treating passengers more and more as if they have nothing better to do but wait around in airports and not get to where the airline promised to bring them.
Again, the airline sets the agreed price or miles for a seat, no one else.
travellots(475): Again, the airline sets the agreed price or miles for a seat, no one else.
Annot: Again, the airline sets the agreed price or miles for a seat, no one else.
The incentives to the airline should be to get all confirmed passengers (regardless of price paid) to the destination promised.
travellots(475): The incentives to the airline should be to get all confirmed passengers (regardless of price paid) to the destination promised.
Annot: The incentives to the airline should be to get all confirmed passengers (regardless of price paid) to the destination promised.
DOT's objective in setting this rule should be to ELIMINATE all bumping, not merely achieve some (unspecified) reduction.
citizen_s(597): DOT's objective in setting this rule should be to ELIMINATE all bumping, not merely achieve some (unspecified) reduction.
Annot: DOT's objective in setting this rule should be to ELIMINATE all bumping, not merely achieve some (unspecified) reduction.
Regardless of how many caveats an airline might state in its contract terms, passengers neither want nor deserve a ticket for an oversold seat.
citizen_s(597): Regardless of how many caveats an airline might state in its contract terms, passengers neither want nor deserve a ticket for an oversold seat.
Annot: Regardless of how many caveats an airline might state in its contract terms, passengers neither want nor deserve a ticket for an oversold seat.
Bumping is a purely economic device that treats passengers as economic units devoid of humanity, like so many other aspects of airline behavior.
citizen_s(597): Bumping is a purely economic device that treats passengers as economic units devoid of humanity, like so many other aspects of airline behavior.
Annot: Bumping is a purely economic device that treats passengers as economic units devoid of humanity, like so many other aspects of airline behavior.
From that objective, it follows that there should be NO cap on compensation
citizen_s(597): From that objective, it follows that there should be NO cap on compensation
Annot: From that objective, it follows that there should be NO cap on compensation
and that the financial penalty to the airline should be strong enough to prevent bumping, not just keep it at some arbitrarily "acceptable" level.
citizen_s(597): and that the financial penalty to the airline should be strong enough to prevent bumping, not just keep it at some arbitrarily "acceptable" level.
Annot: and that the financial penalty to the airline should be strong enough to prevent bumping, not just keep it at some arbitrarily "acceptable" level.
The 100% of the total ticket price for expected arrival within 2 hours later is reasonable.
citizen_s(597): The 100% of the total ticket price for expected arrival within 2 hours later is reasonable.
Annot: The 100% of the total ticket price for expected arrival within 2 hours later is reasonable.
Compensation for a longer delay should be the GREATER of 200% of the total ticket cost or the passenger's demonstrable outofpocket costs resulting from the delay
citizen_s(597): Compensation for a longer delay should be the GREATER of 200% of the total ticket cost or the passenger's demonstrable outofpocket costs resulting from the delay
Annot: Compensation for a longer delay should be the GREATER of 200% of the total ticket cost or the passenger's demonstrable outofpocket costs resulting from the delay
(a) including any higher priced air ticket from the same or another carrier at the same class, and lodging, meals and incidentals at average prevailing prices in that metro area,
citizen_s(597): (a) including any higher priced air ticket from the same or another carrier at the same class, and lodging, meals and incidentals at average prevailing prices in that metro area,
Annot: (a) including any higher priced air ticket from the same or another carrier at the same class, and lodging, meals and incidentals at average prevailing prices in that metro area,

and (b) with the obligation on the passenger to minimize those costs by arranging, with good faith help from the airline, an alternate flight or other means to get him or her to the destination as soon as reasonably practical.

citizen_s(597): and (b) with the obligation on the passenger to minimize those costs by arranging, with good faith help from the airline, an alternate flight or other means to get him or her to the destination as soon as reasonably practical.

Annot: and (b) with the obligation on the passenger to minimize those costs by arranging, with good faith help from the airline, an alternate flight or other means to get him or her to the destination as soon as reasonably practical.
I absolutely agree with citizen_s.
pudef(602): I absolutely agree with citizen_s.
Annot: I absolutely agree with citizen_s.
flying either domestic or international has become the most frustrating part of a travel package.
pudef(602): flying either domestic or international has become the most frustrating part of a travel package.
Annot: flying either domestic or international has become the most frustrating part of a travel package.
It is difficult to feel human on any carrier these days
pudef(602): It is difficult to feel human on any carrier these days
Annot: It is difficult to feel human on any carrier these days
and for the carrier to feel that overbooking is a right in order to protect them from losing money is obscene.
pudef(602): and for the carrier to feel that overbooking is a right in order to protect them from losing money is obscene.
Annot: and for the carrier to feel that overbooking is a right in order to protect them from losing money is obscene.
Recently, when I checked in for my next day flight, I was alerted that my flight had been overbooked.
pudef(602): Recently, when I checked in for my next day flight, I was alerted that my flight had been overbooked.
Annot: Recently, when I checked in for my next day flight, I was alerted that my flight had been overbooked.
This was the first time I have ever been prenotified of actual overbooking
pudef(602): This was the first time I have ever been prenotified of actual overbooking
Annot: This was the first time I have ever been prenotified of actual overbooking
even though I am aware it is considered by the carrier as merely conducting "business as usual".
pudef(602): even though I am aware it is considered by the carrier as merely conducting "business as usual".
Annot: even though I am aware it is considered by the carrier as merely conducting "business as usual".
When did it become okay to sell in good faith something you do not have in inventory to sell?
pudef(602): When did it become okay to sell in good faith something you do not have in inventory to sell?
Annot: When did it become okay to sell in good faith something you do not have in inventory to sell?
Perhaps they can protect any loses by unbundling the amount of oxygen a passenger consumes inflight.
pudef(602): Perhaps they can protect any loses by unbundling the amount of oxygen a passenger consumes inflight.
Annot: Perhaps they can protect any loses by unbundling the amount of oxygen a passenger consumes inflight.
